<tr id="L1"><td><a href="#L1">1</a></td><td>KEIKO:  It's a chipped cup, off-white, with a crack in it. I can see it but I don't remember anything else about it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L2"><td><a href="#L2">2</a></td><td>TARMIN:  (a silver haired man) When you see it, do you hear any sounds?</td></tr>

<tr id="L3"><td><a href="#L3">3</a></td><td>KEIKO:  No, I don't think so. Wait, yes. Humming. Someone's humming.</td></tr>

<tr id="L4"><td><a href="#L4">4</a></td><td>TARMIN:  A woman?</td></tr>

<tr id="L5"><td><a href="#L5">5</a></td><td>KEIKO:  Yes, but I don't know who it is.</td></tr>

<tr id="L6"><td><a href="#L6">6</a></td><td>TARMIN:  Try to touch the cup.</td></tr>

<tr id="L7"><td><a href="#L7">7</a></td><td>KEIKO:  It has a sharp edge where it's chipped.</td></tr>

<tr id="L8"><td><a href="#L8">8</a></td><td>TARMIN:  Is there anything inside the cup?</td></tr>

<tr id="L9"><td><a href="#L9">9</a></td><td>KEIKO:  A liquid, dark.</td></tr>

<tr id="L10"><td><a href="#L10">10</a></td><td>TARMIN:  Like tea?</td></tr>

<tr id="L11"><td><a href="#L11">11</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: seeing herself dipping her finger into it</td></tr>

<tr id="L12"><td><a href="#L12">12</a></td><td>KEIKO:  It's not hot. It's bitter.</td></tr>

<tr id="L13"><td><a href="#L13">13</a></td><td>TARMIN:  There's something else inside the cup.</td></tr>

<tr id="L14"><td><a href="#L14">14</a></td><td>KEIKO:  Yes, a wooden handle.</td></tr>

<tr id="L15"><td><a href="#L15">15</a></td><td>TARMIN:  A spoon?</td></tr>

<tr id="L16"><td><a href="#L16">16</a></td><td>KEIKO:  No, it's more delicate than that.</td></tr>

<tr id="L17"><td><a href="#L17">17</a></td><td>TARMIN:  Reach out for it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L18"><td><a href="#L18">18</a></td><td>KEIKO:  A brush. An ink brush. I hear that humming again.</td></tr>

<tr id="L19"><td><a href="#L19">19</a></td><td>TARMIN:  Keep listening to it, and hold out the brush. See if anyone takes it from you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L20"><td><a href="#L20">20</a></td><td>KEIKO:  It's Obaachan! My grandmother. She's doing ink brush writing. I can remember it now. She used that cup for cleaning the brushes, and it was my job to fill it with water and bring it to the table. I would sit beside her and watch the most beautiful characters come from that brush. And the whole time, she'd be humming to herself. I remember it like it was yesterday.</td></tr>

<tr id="L21"><td><a href="#L21">21</a></td><td>CRUSHER:  That is remarkable. You remembered such vivid detail.</td></tr>

<tr id="L22"><td><a href="#L22">22</a></td><td>KEIKO:  For years I've seen that old cup in my memory but I could never remember what it was or why it was important. Thank you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L23"><td><a href="#L23">23</a></td><td>TARMIN:  You're entirely welcome, young lady. Perhaps someone else would care to try? (to Beverly) You, madam. You're thinking of that first childhood kiss. Would you like to remember more about it?</td></tr>

<tr id="L24"><td><a href="#L24">24</a></td><td>JEV:  Father, you know you're not supposed to probe someone's memory unless they've given you permission.</td></tr>

<tr id="L25"><td><a href="#L25">25</a></td><td>TARMIN:  You are right, but sometimes with a beautiful woman, I can not help myself.</td></tr>

<tr id="L26"><td><a href="#L26">26</a></td><td>LAFORGE:  How about you, Commander? Got any memories you feel like digging up?</td></tr>

<tr id="L27"><td><a href="#L27">27</a></td><td>RIKER:  None that I'd care to share with an audience.</td></tr>

<tr id="L28"><td><a href="#L28">28</a></td><td>KEIKO:  It's getting late. I'd better be going.</td></tr>

